listings.title: Aquarium of the Bay & Ripley's Believe It or Not!
listings.title_as_text: Aquarium of the Bay & Ripley's Believe It or Not!
listings.headline: Aquarium of the Bay & Ripley's Believe It or Not!
listings.summary: Believe it or not, you can explore these two fun attractions with one simple ticket package. Step inside the strange, bizarre and downright unbelievable collection at Ripley's Believe It or Not!, then step into the serene when you surround yourself with 20,000 aquatic animals at Aquarium of the Bay.

listings.title: North Beach Pub Tour
listings.headline: North Beach Pub Tour
listings.summary: From beatniks, blues masters and drunken sailors to hardened fishermen and karaoke kings, North Beach is full of local characters and fanciful folk heroes. Find out about them over a complimentary drink on this San Francisco tour that will get you talking. You'll discover San Francisco's hidden pubs in Little Italy with a local guide, rub shoulders with the regulars at one of North Beach's best bohemian pubs, stroll through the vibrant streets, try an award-winning Northern California craft brew and learn about North Beach's colorful history. Get to Vesuvio Cafe for an experience to broaden your horizons.

listings.title: Gilroy Gardens Family Theme Park
listings.headline: Gilroy Gardens Family Theme Park: Roller Coasters, Mazes and More
listings.summary: Grab the kids and head over to Gilroy Gardens Family Theme Park. You can spend the day riding the roller coasters -- from the thrilling Quicksilver Express Mine Coaster to the mild Sky Trail Monorail -- exploring the beautiful gardens and marveling at the truly bizarre "Circus Trees." And when it's time for a snack you can try some famous Gilroy Garlic Fries, a burger, burrito or splurge on a funnel cake or ice cream sundae. There's something for everyone at the park, making it perfect for the whole family. In May, the Water Oasis is doubling in size!

listings.title: California Academy of Sciences
listings.headline: California Academy of Sciences: Explore the Sea, the Stars, the Rainforests & More
listings.summary: Nestled in the heart of Golden Gate Park, the California Academy of Sciences boasts some pretty impressive credentials: This San Francisco landmark is the only place on Earth that houses an aquarium, planetarium and natural history museum, all under one living roof. Your general admission pass lets you get up close and personal with hundreds of free-flying tropical birds and butterflies inside the four-story living rainforest and gives you access to the award-winning, galaxy-spanning digital shows in the Morrison Planetarium. Animal-lovers can feast their eyes on an albino alligator, a colony of feisty African penguins, and more than 38,000 other live animals in the Steinhart Aquarium. In the new exhibit, Giants of Land and Sea, you can explore Northern California's natural wonders through a variety of experiences: Feel your way through an immersive fog room, keep your balance in an earthquake simulator, virtually ascend to the top of a towering redwood, and see a variety of specimens and fossils. You can learn about everything from meteors to minerals to mankind's evolution ... and that's all before you make your way up to the rolling hills and fields on the rooftop.

listings.headline: Disney Junior Dance Party on Tour!
listings.summary: Are you ready to dance?! Disney Junior Dance Party On Tour Presented by Pull-Ups Training Pants is an all-new interactive live concert experience. Sing and dance along to Disney Junior's greatest hits with your favorite characters. Kids of all ages and their families are all invited to the biggest dance party around, at San Jose's City National Civic. The Disney Junior Dance Party features live appearances by Mickey, Minnie, Goofy, Vampirina, Elena of Avalor, Sofia the First, Fancy Nancy and Doc McStuffins, and magical on screen moments with Puppy Dog Pals, Muppet Babies and the Lion Guard.
listings.title: Disney Junior Dance Party on Tour!
listings.title_as_text: Disney Junior Dance Party on Tour!

listings.title: Aquarium of the Bay
listings.headline: Aquarium of the Bay: San Francisco Bay at Your Fingertips
listings.summary: Visit Aquarium of the Bay for your chance to experience the Bay's fascinating aquatic wildlife up close. Located along San Francisco's walkable waterfront, Aquarium of the Bay is home to more than 20,000 marine animals native to San Francisco Bay, including massive sevengill sharks, luminous moon jellies and bat rays in a touch pool. Four exhibit areas -- Discover the Bay, Under the Bay, Touch the Bay and the river otters exhibit -- provide a scuba diver's view of life in the Bay. Through hands-on learning and interactions with its trained staff, Aquarium of the Bay inspires animal lovers of all ages.

listings.title: Magowan's Infinite Mirror Maze
listings.headline: Get Lost in Magowan's Infinite Mirror Maze
listings.summary: Your Instagram Stories are about to get 100% more psychedelic, thanks to Magowan's Infinite Mirror Maze. This perception-altering attraction at San Francisco's Pier 39 puts a trippy new twist on the old-school House of Mirrors. The entire space is flooded with neon and black lights that illuminate a labyrinth of columns and archways. Spend an hour or three (or more!) wandering about and gazing in awe. Around every corner, you'll see your own astounded reflection as you allow yourself to get gleefully lost in light.

listings.title: The Funniest Show in San Francisco
listings.headline: Sketch Comedy From the Sylvan Boys
listings.summary: The Funniest Show in San Francisco features sketch comedy from local ne'er-do-wells the Sylvan Boys (VICELAND, Sketchfest) This show will include a selection of their best and favorite sketches paired with some tasty new licks. Come on out to PianoFight and see why this is The Funniest Show in San Francisco!

listings.headline: Parties for Singles: Mix, Meet & Mingle
listings.summary: Instead of dealing with the dating apps, and all that winking, swiping and agonizing over the perfect message, why not try finding that special someone by going the time-tested real-life route? The Society for Single Professionals makes it easy with these themed meet-and-mingle parties at The Spinnaker in Sausalito. You'll have the opportunity to connect with a variety of available adult professionals, play games and enjoy appetizers, while they last.
listings.title: Society of Single Professionals: Singles Parties
listings.title_as_text: Society of Single Professionals: Singles Parties

listings.title: SF International Tea Festival
listings.headline: SF International Tea Festival
listings.summary: Tea's been the next big thing since the Third Century and shows no signs of slowing down. In fact, there's more variety and interest in this rich and complex beverage than ever, and you can explore all the latest trends and innovations at the SF International Tea Festival, happening at the Ferry Building Marketplace. Taste dozens of teas from both local and global producers, and peruse the hundreds of different types available for purchase from the marketplace. Some of the biggest names in the beverage biz will be on hand for workshops and lectures, and admission includes a swag bag with samples and your very own souvenir teacup. From black to white to matcha to green, it's all here -- come drink in the goodness.

listings.title: San Francisco Ski & Snowboard Festival
listings.headline: Ski and Snowboard Fest: Deals, Shows, Craft Beer & More
listings.summary: It's that time of year: The air is turning colder, the days are growing shorter, and the mountains are beginning to call to you. And come that first snow, you'll be hitting those slopes. But first, you've got to gear up. Luckily, there's the SnowBomb Ski & Snowboard Festival. This two-day extravaganza will feature great deals on pretty much anything you can take in the snow (probably no sled dogs, though). The actual mountains will most likely have ski lifts, but just in case, you can bone up on your mountaineering skills on the Bear Valley climbing wall. There will also be a BMX and skate ramp show, opportunities to win prizes and more. Plus, if you nab a Powder Pass, you'll get three lift tickets, while VIP tickets will get you access to the beer tastings. Winter is coming ... so make like Jon Snow and get ready at Pier 35 in San Francisco.

listings.title: Luna Mexicana
listings.headline: Oakland Ballet Presents Luna Mexicana
listings.summary: Luna Mexicana is a dance and music celebration of the iconic Mexican holiday, Dia de los Muertos (Day of the Dead). In this show, a young womans dreams revive her relatives and friends, who all dance back to life in the forms of teetering skeletons, skirt swishing girls, a high flying deer dancer and a deathly Bride and Groom. This family-friendly performance is filled with festive dancing, colorful costumes, and vibrant music, including traditional Mexican folk music and witty electronic fusions. You're encouraged to attend in Day of the Dead attire. Gather in the lobby prior to the performance to visit the ofrendas provided by the Oakland Museum of California and enjoy refreshments including tamales, pan de muerto, Mexican hot chocolate and more!

listings.title: Bat Out of Hell
listings.headline: Rock to Meat Loaf Music in Bat Out of Hell
listings.summary: Experience the thrill of London's most spectacular musical as Bat Out of Hell (Winner of Best Musical at the Evening Standard Theatre Awards) brings to life the legendary anthems of Jim Steinman and Meat Loaf, in a critically acclaimed production that combines the magic of a musical, with the immense energy of rock 'n' roll. Join Strat, the forever young leader of rebellious gang 'The Lost,' as he falls in love with Raven, the beautiful daughter of the tyrannical ruler of post-apocalyptic Obsidian. Featuring Meat Loaf's iconic hits including "I'd Do Anything For Love (But I Won't Do That)", "It's All Coming Back To Me Now" and "Paradise By The Dashboard Light," "this is a musical production like no other" (The Upcoming). See it live at the SHN Orpheum Theatre in San Francisco.

listings.title: Alameda Lantern Light Festival
listings.headline: Alameda Lantern Light Festival Celebrates Chinese Culture
listings.summary: Enjoy a spectacular evening of dazzling lights, colors, shapes and themes. The Alameda Lantern Light festival is a six-week celebration (November 30-January 20) of Chinese culture featuring massive lanterns, inspiring performances, and incredible cuisine. A tradition that started over 2,000 years ago, the lantern festival is Chinas most important celebration, marking the return of spring, with the lighting of Chinese lanterns being symbolic of illuminating the future and the reunion of family. While many people picture lanterns being released into the night sky, these enormous lanterns stay firmly on the ground. Each Chinese lantern is custom-built by Chinese artisans and typically takes four weeks and a team of seven to complete. The lanterns appear to be three-dimensional stained glass and are handmade from hundreds of pieces of silky cloth. If you enjoy an evening full of festive lights and amazing sights, bring your family to the opening weekend of the Lantern Light Festival at the Alameda County Fairgrounds, a rare opportunity to witness the majestic skill of the worlds best lantern-makers.

listings.title: Jurassic Park Feature Film with the SF Symphony
listings.title_as_text: "Jurassic Park" Feature Film with the SF Symphony
listings.headline: Jurassic Park Screening With the SF Symphony
listings.summary: Dinosaurs once again roam the earth in director Steven Spielbergs ultimate thrill ride, Jurassic Park. Boasting Academy Award-winning visual effects that deliver stunningly real prehistoric predators even 25 years after its release, this massive blockbuster hit roars to life on the big screen, accompanied by a live accompaniment of John Williams majestic score. Hear the San Francisco Symphony, led by Conductor Constantine Kitsopoulos, at Davies Symphony Hall.

listings.title: That BIG '80s Party
listings.headline: That BIG '80s Party: Dance the Night Away
listings.summary: Break out the leg warmers and miniskirts, it's time for a totally tubular tribute to some of the greatest music of the '80s. DJ Dave Paul is bringing That BIG '80s Party to Public Works in San Francisco -- and he's bringing the decade's best music with him. You never know which classic you're going to hear. But chances are you'll enjoy plenty of hits from the likes of Van Halen, Bon Jovi, U2, The Beastie Boys, INXS, The Cure, Guns N' Roses, Madonna, Men at Work, George Michael and many more.

listings.title: Blind Scream Haunted Houses
listings.headline: Blind Scream Haunted Houses
listings.summary: Scream until you cry ... then you die! Blind Scream presents two terrifying haunted houses for you to lose yourself in at SOMO Village in Rohnert Park. Lil Horrus just wants to have some fun in Lil Horrus' Fun House. Be careful, or you might wind up in his Lil Freak Show. Doc's Horrortorium takes you down Route 666 along a remote area deep in the bayou. You see a roadside attraction and stop to take a look; it's too late to turn around, but hopefully you'll make it out alive! These haunted houses are the perfect way to celebrate the Halloween season -- if you dare.

listings.title: Lea Michele & Darren Criss: The LM/DC Tour
listings.title_as_text: Lea Michele & Darren Criss: "The LM/DC Tour"
listings.headline: Lea Michele & Darren Criss: The LM/DC Tour
listings.summary: Glee alums Lea Michele and Darren Criss team up once again for The LM/DC Tour. The two have shared their powerful pipes and all-in passionate performances on both the small screen and the Broadway musical stage. Now, they'll glide into the San Jose Center for the Performing Arts to share a set filled with original singles, pop gems, songbook standards, show tunes and maybe a musical mashup or two. Watch as Michele and Criss launch into heartfelt versions of personal favorites and even pair up on a few duets.

location.name: San Jose Center for the Performing Arts

venue.name: San Jose Center for the Performing Arts

listings.title: A Noh Christmas Carol
listings.headline: A Noh Christmas Carol: Japanese-Style Adaptation
listings.summary: Theater of Yugen brings A Noh Christmas Carol back to San Francisco in a beloved adaptation that combines the traditional Japanese theater forms of noh, kyogen, kabuki, and the avant-garde dance form butoh to retell the Dickens classic. The story is transposed to early Meiji-era Japan, where Ebezo Sukurooji (Ebenezer Scrooge) receives a visit from his deceased business partner Jakube Mashima (Jacob Marley) warning him to change his miserly ways or be doomed to linger forever as a hungry ghost. The miraculous interventions of the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present, and Yet-To-Come take Sukurooji on a wondrous journey through time and memory to remind him of a life beyond business and profit.

listings.title: Theater of the Damned
listings.headline: Sexy Halloween Event Theater of the Damned
listings.summary: Something's just a little off at Theater of the Damned, a 21+, date-friendly immersive theatrical experience brought to you by the Un-Scripted Theater Company. Bone-chillingly sexy, our performance takes place in two rooms, where you'll encounter tarot card readers, burlesque performers, music, dance, magic ... Theater of the Damned is one-third titillating, one-third terrifying, and one-third hilarious -- a truly unique Halloween experience! And yet ... something isn't right. You can feel it. You can see it on the faces of the servers and performers. You can hear it through the music and the cheers. You can even sense it in the walls. Is it just you? Or just the general eerieness of Halloween? As the show progresses, you begin to wonder, "Are these people running the theater, or is the theater running them?" In either case, you are doomed ... er, destined ... to have an experience you'll remember for eternity. Theater of the Damned features the Un-Scripted Theater Company Ensemble, along with specialty Bay Area acts

listings.title: Darci Lynne Farmer & Friends
listings.headline: Darci Lynne Farmer & Friends: Rocking Around the Christmas Tree
listings.summary: Crazy talented kid Darci Lynne Farmer, the singer-ventriloquist-comedian and recent America's Got Talent champion, is bringing her pals Petunia, Oscar and others to City National Civic in San Jose for Rocking Around the Christmas Tree, a live holiday spectacular. Farmer charmed audiences and judges, including the irascible Simon Cowell, in her winning run on AGT, and the video of her appearance became No. 4 on YouTube's list of the Top Viral Videos of 2017. Now at the ripe old age of 14, she's performed all over the country, including on The Ellen DeGeneres Show, A Very Pentatonix Christmas, Little Big Shots and in Vegas and at the Grand Ole Opry.

listings.headline: Drag Send-Up Golden Girls Live: The Christmas Episodes
listings.summary: The holidays are on their way and the Girls are back! Take four talented drag performers, cast them in two Xmas episodes of the uproarious TV show Golden Girls and you have the perfect holiday event for the entire family. In what has become a yearly tradition, this drag send-up and loving tribute to the characters the entire world has come to know and love, features local drag stars: Heklina (Dorothy), Matthew Martin (Blanche), DArcy Drollinger (Rose), and Holotta Tymes (Sophia).
listings.title: Golden Girls Live: The Christmas Episodes

listings.headline: The Nutcracker: Performed by the San Francisco Youth Ballet Theatre
listings.summary: This magical, full-length version of The Nutcracker features special guest artists performing with the students of the San Francisco Youth Ballet and other bay area dancers. The dance tells the story of young Clara, who dreams that her gift of a toy nutcracker soldier comes to life. Together they experience a grand adventure that takes them through an epic battle with the Mouse King to the Sugar Plum Fairy's magical Kingdom of Sweets. This 2-hour production is geared toward families and is a perfect opportunity to introduce young children to this holiday ballet tradition. The first 200 children will go home with a Nutcracker gift and there will be photo opportunities with different characters after performances.
listings.title: San Francisco Youth Ballet's The Nutcracker
Vonda Shepard
listings.headline: Singer-Songwriter Vonda Shepard (Ally McBeal)
listings.summary: Vonda Shepard returns to Feinsteins at the Nikko with her incredible all-star band: James Ralston (Tina Turner, 22 years!), Jim Hanson (Johnny Cash, Bruce Springsteen!) and Fritz Lewak (Jackson Browne, 26 years!). Vonda will perform songs from throughout her extensive career, including favorites from Ally McBeal, as well as the soulful ballads and funky tunes from her solo albums that brought her to the spotlight to begin with. They will reach deep into Vondas repertoire to inspire you, move you, and by the end of the night, have you on your feet dancing!

listings.headline: Taiwan Philharmonic in Town
listings.summary: After their highly acclaimed U.S. debut in 2016, where the Los Angeles Times deemed them "one of the best," the Taiwan Philharmonic is back in the U.S. to impress Bay Area audiences with their skill and musicality. This concert at Davies Symphony Hall in San Francisco traces the country's classical-music tradition with Taiwanese composer Gordon Chins Dancing Song and works by Barber and Brahms, under the baton of Music Director Shao-Chia L. This concert also marks the SF debut of 24-year old violinist Yu-Chien Tseng, who'll be interpreting Barbers intensely lyrical violin concerto. Yu-Chiens career is rapidly on the rise, as he was recently signed to the legendary record label Deutsche Grammophon.
listings.title: Taiwan Philharmonic

listings.headline: SF Comedy Showcase: The Best Local Comedy at The Punchline
listings.summary: Come see the Punch Line's weekly SF Comedy Showcase, held every Sunday for over 30 years. San Francisco has a rich and vibrant comedy scene, and this weekly show has launched the careers of such comedians as Patton Oswalt, Margaret Cho and Arj Barker, as well as the current flock of rising stars such as W. Kamau Bell and Moshe Kasher. Laugh at a lineup of the Bay Area's top stand-up comics, many of whom have appeared on late-night television, Comedy Central and other esteemed television outlets.
listings.title: SF Comedy Showcase

listings.headline: Powerful Drama Explores Faith & Forgiveness
listings.summary: Cardboard Piano finds the grace notes in "a deeply moving" story of "kindness, love and faith in the midst of a civil war" (Louisville Courier-Journal). Set in a small Ugandan church in 1999, two teenage girls -- one an American, one a local villager -- are in the middle of pledging their love to one another in a secret marriage ceremony when a traumatized child soldier arrives seeking help. This powerful drama from playwright Hansol Jung explores violence and its aftermath, as well as the human capacity for hatred, forgiveness and compassion. Don't miss Cardboard Piano when it takes the stage of San Francisco's New Conservatory Theatre Center.
listings.title: Cardboard Piano

listings.headline: Bear City SF: Stand-Up Comedy in the Mission
listings.summary: Enjoy a secret stand-up comedy show in an intimate show space hidden in the basement of Stuffed, located across the street from the 24th and Mission BART stop in the historic Mission district of San Francisco. These shows feature the best comedians the Bay Area has to offer as well as nationally touring headliners from Conan, Comedy Central and more.
listings.title: Bear City SF: Stand-Up Comedy

listings.headline: No, You're Drunk: The Drinking Game Comedy Show
listings.summary: Drinking games with your friends are fun, but how much funnier would they be if all of your friends were professional comedians? Now's your chance to find out when notorious local comedy group/international jewel thieves Sylvan Productions gets together with their hilarious and super well-known comedian friends, gets them hammered and everyone gets to party with them. No, You're Drunk: The Drinking Game Comedy Show, the latest PianoFight exploit, is a show that's also a drinking game. Actually, it's mostly a drinking game. Hosted by accredited party doctors Justin Gomes and Andrew Moore, No, You're Drunk is rumored to be one of the best ways to spend the 4th Friday of the month (aka the coolest Friday).
listings.title: No, You're Drunk: The Drinking Game Comedy Show
listings.title_as_text: "No, You're Drunk: The Drinking Game Comedy Show"

listings.title: RagTag Improv
listings.headline: A Wild Night Out With RagTag Improv
listings.summary: Catch plenty of high-energy characters, fast-paced scenes and personal absurdities with the comedy stylings of RagTag Improv. Whether it's an entire play invented from scratch using audience suggestions, a series of scenes using every genre imaginable, or some off-the-cuff musical performance, the unpredictability only makes the jokes land harder. Bring friends and settle in for a night of laughs at Stage Werx as the talented cast of improvisers draw on San Francisco's brand of energy to deliver unscripted and unexpected comedy -- always different, but reliably hilarious.

listings.headline: Pianist Cecile Licad Benefit Concert
listings.summary: San Francisco's Mission Dolores Basilica Church is celebrating its 100th anniversary in December of 2018, and they've already picked out a present -- a new Steinway concert piano, one that's worthy of the Basilica's reputation as a premier performing arts destination and center of worship. To aid them in their cause, Cecile Licad, called "a pianist's pianist" by The New Yorker, commands the keyboard in this benefit concert. The virtuosic Licad, who made her debut at the age of seven with her home country's Philippine Philharmonic Orchestra, boasts a huge repertoire of classic, romantic and contemporary pieces and is a successful recording artist.
listings.title: Pianist Cecile Licad

listings.headline: martha & monica at Berkeley Chamber Performances
listings.summary: This duo fuses music and emotion into compelling narratives to engage the listener. This evening's cello/piano program of beloved masterpieces and contemporary works demonstrates the breadth of martha & monica's (Hadley McCarroll, piano & Monica Scott, cello) repertoire that will evoke your curiosity and comfort you like an old friend.
listings.title: martha & monica

listings.headline: Lisa Rothman's Solo Show: Dragon in the Drop-Off Lane
listings.summary: In Dragon in the Drop-Off Lane, Lisa Rothman spins a hilarious fairy tale fit for any parent. After her kids dodge bullets at the local park, Lisa takes them to the Winter Solstice Carnival, where she must now dodge a gang of PTA moms in Lululemon, a fire-breathing dragon and, worst of all, her father. Of course, no fairy tale would be complete without a fairy godmother to help her sort through her parenting choices. See Rothmans unmatched storytelling skills in action when her latest solo show comes to The Marsh in Berkeley.
listings.title: Lisa Rothman: Dragon in the Drop-Off Lane
listings.title_as_text: Lisa Rothman: "Dragon in the Drop-Off Lane"

listings.title: Emperor Norton's Fantastic San Francisco Time Machine
listings.title_as_text: Emperor Norton's Fantastic San Francisco Time Machine
listings.headline: Emperor Norton's Fantastic SF Time Machine Walking Tour
listings.summary: Take a tour through San Francisco's history with one of its most colorful characters. Emperor Norton was a prominent businessman who lost it all on a bad investment. He responded to his failure by declaring himself "Emperor of the United States and Protector of Mexico." Rather than dismissing him, San Francisco embraced him, treating him as royalty and accepting his self-created currency. Tour guide Joseph Amster incorporates his journalistic and acting talents to provide a one-of-a-kind tour, taking on the persona of Emperor Norton and introducing you to the history of the city's most unique and interesting sites through the eyes of this larger-than-life unofficial city mascot.

listings.headline: Family Fave The Wizard of Oz
listings.summary: Head on down the yellow brick road with the Scarecrow, Tin Man, Cowardly Lion, Dorothy and her little dog, Toto, too, as The Wizard of Oz blows its way into the Julia Morgan Theater for an all-new production by the Berkeley Playhouse. When a storm hits her family farm in Kansas, young Dorothy is swept over the rainbow to a magical land where scarecrows talk, tin men sing, lions (barely) roar, and where one very wicked witch rules the skies. One of the most treasured stories of the 20th century, filled with the songs that made the movie an instant classic, this musical journey of finding home -- and yourself -- is one of this holiday seasons must-see family events.
listings.title: The Wizard of Oz

listings.headline: Cobb's Holiday Comedy Bash: Kabir "Kabeezy" Singh
listings.summary: Cobb's presents their biggest show of the year, the annual Holiday Comedy Bash. This year's headliner is Kabir "Kabeezy" Singh, a fast-rising comedy star who's been called "The Next Big Indian Comedian" by India West and "One of the Must-See Stand-Up Comedians in the U.S." by TV Asia. Kabir is a huge crowdpleaser with an abundance of energy, an in-your-face attitude and clever material. He's won numerous comedy contests, including taking first place two years in a row at the Bay Area Stand-Up Comedy Competition, opened for top stars like Russell Peters, Dave Chappelle and Dane Cook, and taped sets for Comedy Central's Gabriel Iglesias' Stand-Up Revolution and Starz's StannDupp. Don't miss the end-of-the-year fun at Cobb's Comedy Club in San Francisco.
listings.title: Cobb's Holiday Comedy Bash Starring Kabir "Kabeezy" Singh
listings.title_as_text: Cobb's "Holiday Comedy Bash" Starring Kabir "Kabeezy" Singh
